3D%5C%22867%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPay%20attention%20to%20unit%20pricing%20to%20find%20the%20cheapest%20option%20by%20the%20pound%20or%20ounce.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EShrinkflation%20describes%20how%20companies%20slowly%20and%20subtly%20decrease%20the%20size%20of%20the%20product%20offered%20without%20decreasing%20the%20price.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EShrinkflation%20gets%20even%20worse%20in%20response%20to%20lingering%20inflation.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBe%20on%20the%20lookout%20for%20new%20packaging%2C%20shop%20store%20brands%2C%20and%20keep%20track%20of%20the%20unit%20pricing%20to%20avoid%20losing%20money%20to%20shrinkflation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EShrinkflation%20has%20gotten%20so%20bad%20that%20President%20Biden%20talked%20about%20it%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstate-of-union-speech-biden-congress-gaza-abortion-israel-aid-2024-3%5C%22%3Ehis%20State%20of%20the%20Union%20address%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20unfamiliar%20with%20the%20term%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcorporatefinanceinstitute.com%2Fresources%2Feconomics%2Fshrinkflation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshrinkflation%3C%2Fa%3E%20refers%20to%20companies%20slowly%20and%20subtly%20decreasing%20the%20size%20of%20their%20products%20without%20decreasing%20the%20price.%20It's%20actually%20a%20form%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-inflation%5C%22%3Einflation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Manufacturers%20know%20that%20customers%20would%20most%20likely%20spot%20a%20price%20increase%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20on%20everyday%20items%20%E2%80%94%20so%20they%20decide%20to%20reduce%20the%20size%20of%20the%20product%20instead%2C%20thinking%20that%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20shrinkage%20will%20probably%20go%20unnoticed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20price%20of%20groceries%20have%20increased%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fcpi%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E20%25%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20with%20shrinkflation%20in%20play%20too%2C%20you're%20getting%20less%20for%20your%20money%20than%20ever%20before.%20The%20shrinkflation%20effect%20is%20most%20commonly%20seen%20in%20potato%20chips%2C%20cookies%2C%20cereal%2C%20candy%2C%20paper%20products%2C%20and%20even%20shampoo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%204%20ways%20to%20minimize%20the%20impact%20of%20shrinkflation%20and%20get%20the%20best%20bang%20for%20your%20buck%20at%20the%20grocery%20store%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Check%20alternatives%20to%20your%20favorite%20brand%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20notice%20that%20the%20brand%20that%20you%20normally%20buy%20has%20gotten%20smaller%20in%20size%2C%20but%20the%20price%20hasn't%20changed%20or%20the%20price%20may%20have%20even%20increased%2C%20it%20may%20be%20time%20to%20switch%20brands.%20A%20competing%20brand%20may%20not%20have%20changed%20their%20packaging%20or%20downsized%20yet%2C%20and%20you%20will%20still%20be%20able%20to%20get%20the%20right%20value%20for%20what%20you%20are%20paying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Buy%20store%20brands%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStore%20brands%20typically%20have%20cheaper%20prices%20than%20the%20major%20brands%20that%20you%20find%20on%20store%20shelves.%20Think%20Kirkland%20brand%20at%20Costco%20or%20the%20store%20brands%20in%20Walgreens%20or%20Walmart.%20Because%20store%20brands%20are%20already%20generally%20the%20cheaper%20options%2C%20they%20will%20also%20be%20slower%20to%20repackage%20or%20downsize%20their%20products.%20Think%20about%20shopping%20for%20what%20you%20can%20at%20stores%20like%20Costco%20or%20BJs%20where%20you%20can%20buy%20even%20larger-sized%20items%20that%20will%20last%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Notice%20the%20packaging%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20quick%20way%20to%20notice%20shrinkflation%20is%20by%20spotting%20a%20repackaging%20of%20the%20item%20or%20a%20catchy%20new%20slogan.%20This%20could%20be%20a%20sign%20that%20the%20company%20has%20made%20a%20change%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20change%20may%20be%20the%20size%20of%20the%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERemember%2C%20the%20manufacturer%20is%20not%20going%20to%20tell%20you%20it's%20doing%20this%2C%20so%20be%20on%20the%20lookout%20for%20differences%20in%20the%20look%20or%20the%20weight%20of%20the%20product.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Keep%20track%20of%20unit%20pricing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStores%20have%20the%20unit%20pricing%20for%20most%20products%20listed%20right%20on%20the%20shelves.%20You'll%20see%20it%20listed%20as%20price%20per%20pound%20or%20price%20per%20ounce.%20For%20example%2C%20a%2030-ounce%20jar%20of%20pickles%20that%20costs%20%248%20would%20list%20a%20unit%20price%20of%20%240.27%20per%20ounce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnit%20pricing%20can%20help%20you%20find%20the%20cheapest%20option%20when%20similar%20products%20have%20different%20weights%20and%20prices.%20If%20you%20have%20two%20different%20brands%20of%20similar%20products%2C%20you%20may%20have%20to%20use%20your%20calculator%20to%20determine%20which%20one%20is%20cheaper%20or%20a%20better%20value%20for%20your%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-budget%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebudget%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBuild%20a%20Budget%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-budgeting-apps%5C%22%3Ebest%20budgeting%20apps%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20help%20you%20get%20your%20finances%20in%20order%20and%20track%20your%20monthly%20spending.%20Top%20offers%20include%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Frocket-money-app-review%5C%22%3ERocket%20Money%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww