s%20a%2065%25%20chance%20of%20a%20recession%20in%20the%20next%20two%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Federal%20Reserve%20should%20wait%20until%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%20year%20before%20cutting%20interest%20rates%2C%20JP%20Morgan%20Chase%20CEO%20Jamie%20Dimon%20said%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20think%20they%20have%20to%20be%20data-dependent.%20If%20I%20were%20them%2C%20I%20would%20wait%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dimon%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.afr.com%2Fchanticleer%2Fjamie-dimon-on-recession-bubbles-and-a-nerve-wracking-us-election-20240312-p5fbr8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAustralian%20Financial%20Review%20Business%20Summit.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey%20can%20always%20cut%20it%20quickly%20and%20dramatically%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dimon%2C%20who%20dialed%20remotely%20into%20the%20event.%20%26quot%3BTheir%20credibility%20is%20a%20little%20bit%20at%20stake%20here.%20I%20would%20even%20wait%20past%20June%20and%20let%20it%20all%20sort%20out.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDimon's%20caution%20is%20based%20on%20his%20view%20that%20even%20though%20the%20US%20economy%20is%20%26quot%3Bkind%20of%20booming%26quot%3B%20right%20now%2C%20there's%20still%20a%20risk%20it%20could%20enter%20a%20recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20has%20cut%20interest%20rates%20multiple%20times%20since%20March%202022%20to%20cool%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-cpi-consumer-price-index-january-housing-food-energy-prices-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20trying%20to%20steer%20the%20economy%20into%20making%20what's%20known%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bsoft%20landing%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20where%20the%20economy%20cools%20enough%20to%20bring%20inflation%20down%20without%20falling%20into%20a%20recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20economy%20appears%20resilient%20even%20after%20numerous%20rounds%20of%20interest%20rate%20hikes.%20%3Ca