C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F03%2F11%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Ffaa-audit-boeing-737-max.html%3Fsmtyp%3Dcur%26smid%3Dtw-nytimes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20regulator%20then%20observed%20mechanics%20at%20Spirit%20AeroSystems%2C%20which%20builds%20the%20fuselage%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-737-max-safety-record-crashes-issues-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBoeing's%20737%20Max%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20cleaning%20up%20using%20a%20wet%20cheesecloth%2C%20per%20The%20Times'%20Mark%20Walker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20findings%20were%20part%20of%20a%20six-week%20audit%20documented%20in%20a%20set%20of%20FAA%20presentation%20slides%20upon%20which%20The%20Times%20based%20its%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20slides%20said%20that%20Boeing%20had%20failed%2033%20of%2089%20product%20audits%20related%20to%20737%20Max%20production%2C%20while%20Spirit%20failed%20seven%20of%2013%20audits%2C%20per%20The%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGlobal%20scrutiny%20is%20building%20on%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20737%20Max's%20fuselage%20after%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falaska-boeing-737-max-9-door-blowout-company-response-earnings-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edoor%20plug%20on%20an%20Alaska%20Airlines%3C%2Fa%3E%20flight%20blew%20out%20in%20January%20while%20the%20aircraft%20was%20still%20midair.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20incident%20triggered%20a%20push%20to%20investigate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjohn-barnett-boeing-manager-whistleblower-dead-self-inflicted-wound-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esafety%20standards%20at%20Boeing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20had%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Flocal%2Ftrafficandcommuting%2Flong-before-the-max-disasters-boeing-had-a-history-of-failing-to-fix-safety-problems%2F2019%2F06%2F26%2Fb4f5f720-86ee-11e9-a870-b9c411dc4312_story.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccused%20of%20quality%20assurance%20lapses%20for%20several%20years.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Times%20reported%20that%20most%20of%20the%20issues%20flagged%20by%20the%20FAA%20involved%20manufacturing%20staff%20not%20following%20approved%20procedures%2C%20while%20some%20involved%20issues%20with%20documenting%20quality%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20note%20for%20the%20liquid%20soap%20incident%20said%20the%20door%20seal%20fitting%20instructions%20were%20%26quot%3Bvague%20and%20unclear%20on%20what%20specifications%20or%20actions%20are%20to%20be%20followed%20or%20recorded%20by%20the%20mechanic%2C'%26quot%3B%20per%20The%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20The%20Times'%20report%2C%20Boeing%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20it%20would%20%26quot%3Bcontinue%20to%20implement%20immediate%20changes%20and%20develop%20a%20comprehensive%20action%20plan%20to%20strengthen%20safety%20and%20quality.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20squarely%20focused%20on%20taking%20significant%2C%20demonstrated%20action%20with%20transparency%20at%20every%20turn%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpirit%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Spirit%20told%20The%20Times%20the%20firm%20is%20%26quot%3Breviewing%20all%20identified%20nonconformities%20for%20corrective%20action.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20comes%20after%20the%20FAA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fi%2Fbroadcasts%2F1MnxnMXwdgdJO%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20late%20February%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20had%20found%20quality%20control%20issues%20at%20Boeing%2C%20and%20gave%20the%20aviation%20company%2090%20days%20to%20submit%20a%20plan%20for%20fixing%20these%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20B