determined%20bias%20in%20the%20committee%E2%80%99s%20view.%E2%80%9D%20His%20exclusion%2C%20he%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20seem%20like%20an%20attempt%20to%20ensure%20a%20majority%20rather%20than%20relying%20on%20consensus%20building.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELavasa%20has%20been%20explicit%20about%20failing%20to%20follow%20why%20the%20government%20initially%20equated%20the%20EC%20and%20the%20CEC%20with%20the%20Cabinet%20Secretary%2C%20but%20later%20displayed%20%E2%80%9Cmuddled%20thinking%E2%80%9D%20having%C2%A0%20apparently%20%E2%80%9Cstruck%20a%20bargain%E2%80%9D%20by%20restoring%20the%20equivalence%20of%20EC%2FCEC%20with%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20but%20then%20mysteriously%20reversing%20the%20parity%20in%20the%20removal%20process%20of%20the%20EC%20and%20CEC%2C%20to%20the%20original%20one%2C%20where%20only%20the%20CEC%20is%20insulated%20from%20routine%20removal%20process%2C%20not%20other%20members%20of%20the%20EC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20writes%20that%20he%20finds%20it%20%E2%80%9Cequally%20confounding%E2%80%9D%20why%20the%20Cabinet%20Secretary%20has%20been%20replaced%20%E2%80%9Cby%20the%20Law%20Minister%20as%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20Search%20Committee.%E2%80%9D%20The%20original%20provision%20in%20the%20new%20law%20to%20appoint%20ECs%2C%20provided%20for%20%E2%80%9Ctwo%20other%20members%E2%80%A6%20having%20knowledge%20and%20experience%20in%20matters%20relating%20to%20elections.%E2%80%9D%20The%20purpose%20of%20changing%20the%20chairmanship%20and%20dropping%20%E2%80%9Chaving%20knowledge%20and%20experience%20in%20matters%20relating%20to%20elections%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20case%20of%20the%20members%2C%20has%20been%20called%20out%20by%20Lavasa%2C%20as%20he%20says%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20thought%20process%20behind%20the%20other%20provisions%20as%20proposed%20and%20amended%20beats%20my%20bureaucratic%20understanding%2C%20evolved%20during%20four%20decades%20in%20the%20government.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Five%20Reasons%20There's%20a%20Dark%20Cloud%20Over%20Election%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20Transparency%20and%20Functioning%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ffive-reasons-theres-a-dark-cloud-over-election-commissions-transparency-and-functioning%5C%22%3EFive%20Reasons%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20Dark%20Cloud%20Over%20Election%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20Transparency%20and%20Functioning%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELavasa%E2%80%99s%20four%20decades%20in%20government%20should%20have%20ended%20with%20him%20being%20CEC%2C%20but%20he%20found%20himself%20in%20Manila%E2%80%99s%20Asian%20Development%20Bank%20instead%2C%20after%20the%202019%20polls.%20In%20August%202020%2C%20he%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpresident-kovind-accepts-ashok-lavasas-resignation-from-post-of-election-commissioner%5C%22%3Eresigned%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0just%20months%20short%20of%20becoming%20the%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20in%20April%202021.%20His%20resignation%20came%20a%20year%20after%20he%20became%20the%20only%20member%20of%20the%20three-member%20election%20commission%20to%20rule%20that%20Modi%20had%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fec-record-dissent-note-order-lavasa%5C%22%3E%C2%A0violated%20the%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0while%20campaigning%20for%20the%202019%20general%20election.%20His%20demand%20that%20dissent%20notes%20should%20be%20recorded%20in%20the%20commission%E2%80%99s%20orders%20on%20model%20code%20violations%20was%20rejected%20with%20a%20majority%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0had%20reported%20that%20just%20weeks%20after%20his%20dissent%2C%20Lavasa%E2%80%99s%20personal%20mobile%20number%20was%20placed%20on%20the%20list%20of%20numbers%20found%20on%20a%20leaked%20database%20of%20likely%20targets%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpegasus-project-ashok-lavasa-narendra-modi-amit-shah-model-code-of-conduct%5C%22%3EPegasus%20spyware.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%20in%202019%2C%20Lavasa%E2%80%99s%20wife%2C%20son%20and%20sister%20were%20placed%20under%20the%20scanner%20of%20various%20investigative%20agencies.%20Writing%20in%20a%20national%20daily%20in%20December%202019%2C%20months%20prior%20to%20his%20resignation%2C%20Lavasa%20said%20there%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cprice%20for%20honesty%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20price%20for%20honesty%20as%20for%20everything%20else%20in%20life.%20Being%20prepared%20to%20pay%20that%20price%2C%20directly%20or%20by%20way%20of%20collateral%20damage%2C%20is%20part%20of%20the%20honest%20act%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20the%20V-Dem%20(or%20Varieties%20of%20Democracy)%20report%20stated%20that%20India%20dropped%20down%20to%20an%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsince-2018-india-has-remained-an-electoral-autocracy-v-dem-report%5C%22%3Eelectoral%20autocracy%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%202018%20and%20remained%20in%20this%20category%20till%20the%20end%20of%202023.%20More%20worryingly%2C%20under%20its%20clean%20elections%20index%2C%20the%20report%20said%20that%20India%20was%20among%2018%20countries%20in%20which%20the%20indicator%20for%20free%20and%20fairness%20of%20elections%20deteriorated%20substantially%20and%20significantly.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710216780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F11%2Fashok-lavasa.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fashok-lavasa-finds-modi-govts-exclusion-of-cji-from-ec-appointment-panel-hard-to-fathom%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Lavasa%20has%20termed%20changes%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court-suggested%20law%20on%20the%20manner%20of%20picking%20new%20election%20commissioners%20%E2%80%9Cconfounding%E2%80%9D%20and%20one%20geared%20to%20create%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpredetermined%20bias%20in%20the%20committee%E2%80%99s%20view%E2%80%9D%2C%20not%20a%20drive%20to%20consensu