-election-commission-of-india-down-to-just-one-member-on-election-eve%5C%22%3E%20resignation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20weeks%20before%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20are%20due%20with%20no%20clear%20reasons%20communicated%2C%20has%20once%20again%20cast%20a%20cloud%20on%20the%20transparency%20and%20functioning%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20Goel%E2%80%99s%20resignation%2C%20the%20three-member%20Election%20Commission%20is%20down%20to%20just%20one%20member%20%E2%80%93%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20Rajiv%20Kumar.%20Earlier%20in%20February%2C%20election%20commissioner%20Anup%20Pandey%20retired%20from%20office%20but%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20replaced.%20According%20to%20reports%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20will%20chair%20a%20meeting%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fadhir-informed-of-ec-search-committee-meeting-as-opposition-raises-questions-on-goel-resignation%5C%22%3Eappoint%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethe%20two%20election%20commissioners%20later%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20poll%20body%2C%20an%20autonomous%20one%2C%20is%20a%20pivotal%20part%20of%20the%20India%20democracy%20story%2C%20as%20it%20is%20entrusted%20with%20conducting%20elections%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20Rajya%20Sabha%20and%20state%20assemblies%2C%20and%20the%20offices%20of%20the%20president%20and%20vice-president%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECrucially%2C%20it%20is%20also%20in%20charge%20of%20ensuring%20that%20political%20parties%20adhere%20to%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feci.gov.in%2Fmcc%2F%5C%22%3E%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20appealing%20for%20votes%20that%20prohibits%20the%20use%20of%20religion%2C%20hate%20speech%2C%20caste%20or%20communal%20feelings%2C%20corrupt%20practices%2C%20and%20also%20bars%20the%20party%20in%20power%20(whether%20at%20Centre%20or%20state)%20from%20using%20government%20machinery%20for%20election%20purposes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20the%20V-Dem%20(or%20Varieties%20of%20Democracy)%20report%20stated%20that%20India%20dropped%20down%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsince-2018-india-has-remained-an-electoral-autocracy-v-dem-report%5C%22%3Eelectoral%20autocracy%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202018%20and%20remained%20in%20this%20category%20till%20the%20end%20of%202023.%20More%20worryingly%2C%20under%20its%20clean%20elections%20index%2C%20the%20report%20said%20that%20India%20was%20among%2018%20countries%20in%20which%20the%20indicator%20for%20free%20and%20fairness%20of%20elections%20deteriorated%20substantially%20and%20significantly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20five%20reasons%20why%20the%20independence%2C%20transparency%20and%20functioning%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20has%20come%20under%20scrutiny%20in%20the%20last%20five%20years%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Electoral%20bonds%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20role%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20has%20come%20under%20the%20scanner%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20declaring%20anonymous%20electoral%20bonds%20as%20%E2%80%9Cunconstitutional%E2%80%9D%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felectoral-bonds-case-sc-dismisses-sbis-plea-for-extension-says-disclose-information-by-march-12%5C%22%3Edismissed%20the%20plea%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(SBI)%20for%20an%20extension%20in%20complying%20with%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20earlier%20directive%20on%20providing%20details%20related%20to%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20asked%20the%20Election%20Commission%20%E2%80%9Cto%20compile%20the%20information%20and%20publish%20the%20information%20on%20their%20website%20no%20later%20than%20by%205%20PM%20on%20March%2015%2C%202024.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20initially%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felection-commission-has-no-comments-on-landmark-verdict-on-electoral-bonds-how-it-changed-its-stance%5C%22%3Erefusing%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20comment%2C%20three%20days%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order%20last%20month%2C%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20Rajiv%20Kumar%20said%20that%20the%20commission%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commission-will-follow-supreme-courts-directions-on-electoral-bonds-cec%5C%22%3Efollow%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20directions%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felection-commission-has-no-comments-on-landmark-verdict-on-electoral-bonds-how-it-changed-its-stance%5C%22%3Echanging%20stance%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20electoral%20bonds%20has%20raised%20eyebrows.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20the%20scheme%20being%20introduced%20in%202018%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20had%20written%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Law%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffpost.com%2Farchive%2Fin%2Fentry%2Felectoral-bonds-narendra-modi-election-commission-opposition-arun-jaitley_in_5dce3cd1e4b01f982eff5c62%5C%22%3Ewarning%20against%20electoral%20bonds%20and%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20would%20help%20political%20parties%20hide%20illegal%20donations%20from%20foreign%20sources%20and%20might%20even%20%E2%80%9Clead%20to%20increased%20use%20of%20black%20money%20for%20political%20funding%20through%20shell%20companies%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20the%20EC%20suddenly%20changed%20its%20position%20and%20opposed%20a%20plea%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20for%20a%20stay%20on%20the%20release%20of%20the%20fresh%20set%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20from%20April%201%2C%202021%20for%20the%20assembly%20elections%20which%20were%20scheduled%20that%20year%20in%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Kerala%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Assam%20and%20Puducherry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20total%20number%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2012%2C008%20crore%20sold%20between%202017-2018%20and%202022-2023%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20received%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-are-illegal-now-but-who-benefited-for-the-6-years-they-lasted%5C%22%3Enearly%2055%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20Rs%206%2C564%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20EVMs%20and%20VVPATs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Election%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20use%20of%20Voter%20Verifiable%20Paper%20Audit%20Trail%20(VVPAT)%20tallies%20and%20Electronic%20Voting%20Machines%20(EVMs)%20has%20come%20under%20question%20since%20the%20poll%20body%20started%20its%20country-wide%20use%20for%20the%20first%20time%20during%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20all%20EVMs%20are%20covered%20by%20VVPATs.%20A%20VVPAT%20lets%20a%20voter%20see%20a%20paper%20slip%20printed%20in%20the%20VVPAT%20for%20a%20period%20of%20seven%20seconds%2C%20displaying%20the%20name%20and%20the%20symbol%20of%20the%20selected%20candidate.%20It%20then%20drops%20into%20a%20sealed%20drop%20box%20of%20the%20VVPAT.%20According%20to%20Supreme%20Court%20guidelines%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20verifies%20VVPAT%20slips%20in%20five%20randomly%20selected%20polling%20stations%20in%20each%20assembly%20constituency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ffour-years-since-general-election-centre-yet-to-obtain-info-on-evm-vvpat-discrepancy%5C%22%3Eparliamentary%20panel%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20was%20yet%20to%20provide%20a%20reply%20for%20the%20last%20four%20years%20after%20it%20promised%20parliament%20that%20it%20would%20obtain%20information%20from%20the%20Election%20Commission%20about%20possible%20discrepancies%20between%20the%20EVMs%20and%20VVPATs%20during%20the%202019%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20election%20watchdog%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fpaper-trial-must-for-free-and-fair-elections-adr-moves-sc-for-counting-of-vvpats%5C%22%3E%20filed%20a%20petition%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20seeking%20the%20counting%20of%20all%20VVPATs%20in%20the%202023%20assembly%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20PIL%20said%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpaper%20trail%E2%80%9D%20is%20an%20indispensable%20requirement%20of%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20and%20that%20the%20ECI%20should%20be%20directed%20to%20count%20all%20VVPAT%20slips.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20September%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20in%20an%20affidavit%20said%20to%20the%20court%20that%20100%25%20verification%20of%20EVMs%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Felections%2Findia%2Fwould-mean-reverting-to-old-ballot-system-ec-opposes-100-vvpat-verification-in-supreme-court-2676774%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cregressive%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20would%20imply%20going%20back%20to%20paper%20ballots.%20Crucially%20it%20also%20said%20there%20was%20no%20%E2%80%9Cfundamental%20right%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20voters%20to%20verify%20through%20VVPATS%20that%20their%20votes%20had%20been%20%E2%80%9Crecorded%20as%20cast%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Ccounted%20as%20recorded%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-evm-vvpat-tally-election-commission-general-elections-241567%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAhead%2520of%2520the%25202024%2520general%2Cwithout%2520any%2520%2527big%2520advantage%2527.%5C%22%3Eorally%20observed%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20enhancing%20the%20scale%20of%20EVM%20data%20cross-checking%20against%20VVPAT%20records%20would%20increase%20the%20election%20commission%E2%80%99s%20work%20without%20any%20%E2%80%9Cbig%20advantage%E2%80%9D%2C%20reported%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpposition%20parties%20have%20also%20raised%20questions%20on%20the%20use%20of%20EVMs%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fjairam-ramesh-evm-concerns-chief-election-commissioner-letter-ec-9091381%2F%5C%22%3Eurged%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Election%20Commission%20to%20intervene.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Arun%20Goel%E2%80%99s%20appointment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoel%E2%80%99s%20resignation%20has%20raised%20serious%20questions%2C%20but%20his%20appointment%20too%20was%20not%20free%20of%20controversy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202022%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20questioned%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-questions-tearing-hurry-in-union-govts-appointment-of-arun-goel-as-ec%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Ctearing%20hurry%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20which%20Goel%20was%20appointed%20as%20election%20commissioner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoel%2C%20a%20Punjab%20cadre%20IAS%20officer%2C%20was%20appointed%20as%20election%20commissioner%20on%20November%2019%2C%202022%20%E2%80%93%20just%20a%20day%20after%20he%20resigned%20from%20the%20Indian%20Administrative%20Service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%20said%20the%201985-batch%20IAS%20officer%20got%20voluntary%20retirement%20from%20service%20(VRS)%20in%20just%20a%20single%20day%2C%20his%20file%20was%20cleared%20by%20the%20Union%20law%20ministry%20overnight%2C%20a%20panel%20of%20four%20names%20was%20put%20up%20before%20the%20prime%20minister%20and%20Goel%E2%80%99s%20name%20got%20the%20nod%20from%20the%20president%20within%2024%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202023%2C%20however%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20dismissed%20a%20PIL%20challenging%20his%20appointment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoel%20was%20in%20line%20to%20be%20the%20next%20CEC%20after%20incumbent%20Rajiv%20Kumar%20demits%20office%20in%20February%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20New%20law%20to%20appoint%20EC%20and%20CEC%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20officials%20who%20will%20be%20appointed%20after%20Goel%20and%20Panday%E2%80%99s%20departures%20will%20be%20the%20first%20under%20the%20new%20law%20passed%20by%20parliament%20during%20the%20winter%20session%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20December%2C%20parliament%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Flok-sabha-passes-election-commissioners-bill%5C%22%3Epassed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20controversial%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20Other%20Election%20Commissioners%20(Appointment%2C%20Conditions%20of%20Service%20and%20Term%20of%20Office)%20Bill%2C%202023%20that%20provides%20for%20the%20appointment%2C%20salary%20and%20removal%20of%20the%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20(CEC)%20and%20election%20commissioners%20(ECs)%2C%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Frajya-sabha-passes-bill-election-commissioners-opposition-appointment%5C%22%3Eabsence%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20terms%20of%20the%20new%20legislation%2C%20the%20government-dominated%20selection%20committee%20will%20fill%20vacant%20slots%20on%20the%20commission%20from%20candidates%20short-listed%20by%20a%20search%20committee%20headed%20by%20the%20Union%20cabinet%20secretary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20was%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fumpire-cannot-be-subordinate-to-team-captain%5C%22%3Eintroduced%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20monsoon%20session%20in%20August%20and%20came%20months%20after%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-says-committee-of-pm-leader-of-opposition-cji-should-appoint-election-commissioners%5C%22%3Econstitution%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20in%20March%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20election%20commissioners%20should%20be%20appointed%20by%20the%20president%20based%20on%20advice%20from%20a%20committee%20comprising%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20opposition%20(LOP)%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%20(CJI).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20legislation%20states%20that%20the%20CEC%20and%20the%20ECs%20(the%20number%20of%20ECs%20will%20be%20determined%20periodically%20by%20the%20president)%20will%20be%20appointed%20by%20the%20president%20based%20on%20the%20recommendations%20of%20a%20selection%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20consists%20of%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20a%20cabinet%20minister%20and%20the%20LOP%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20(or%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20single%20largest%20opposition%20party).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20legislation%20has%20raised%20questions%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fumpire-cannot-be-subordinate-to-team-captain%5C%22%3Eoverriding%20executive%20control%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20poll%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Ashok%20Lavasa%E2%80%99s%20dissent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202020%2C%20election%20commissioner%20Ashok%20Lavasa%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpresident-kovind-accepts-ashok-lavasas-resignation-from-post-of-election-commissioner%5C%22%3Eresigned%3C%2Fa%3E%20just%20months%20short%20of%20becoming%20the%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20in%20April%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20resignation%20came%20a%20year%20after%20he%20became%20the%20only%20member%20of%20the%20three-member%20election%20commission%20to%20rule%20that%20Modi%20had%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fec-record-dissent-note-order-lavasa%5C%22%3E%20violated%20the%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20campaigning%20for%20the%202019%20general%20election.%20His%20demand%20that%20dissent%20notes%20should%20be%20recorded%20in%20the%20commission%E2%80%99s%20orders%20on%20model%20code%20violations%20was%20rejected%20with%20a%20majority%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehad%20reported%20that%20just%20weeks%20after%20his%20dissent%2C%20Lavasa%E2%80%99s%20personal%20mobile%20number%20was%20placed%20on%20the%20list%20of%20numbers%20found%20on%20a%20leaked%20database%20of%20likely%20targets%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpegasus-project-ashok-lavasa-narendra-modi-amit-shah-model-code-of-conduct%5C%22%3EPegasus%20spyware.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%20in%202019%2C%20Lavasa%E2%80%99s%20wife%2C%20son%20and%20sister%20were%20placed%20under%20the%20scanner%20of%20various%20investigative%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20he%20was%20in%20line%20to%20head%20the%20poll%20body%2C%20Lavasa%20opted%20to%20quit%20the%20Election%20Commission%20in%202020%20and%20join%20the%20Asian%20Development%20Bank%20as%20vice-president%2C%20where%20he%20currently%20works.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWriting%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20December%202019%2C%20mere%20months%20prior%20to%20his%20resignation%2C%20Lavasa%20said%20there%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cprice%20for%20honesty%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20price%20for%20honesty%20as%20for%20everything%20else%20in%20life.%20Being%20prepared%20to%20pay%20that%20price%2C%20directly%20or%20by%20way%20of%20collateral%20damage%2C%20is%20part%20of%20the%20honest%20act%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20democratic%20record%2C%20a%20rare%20one%20in%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20is%20premised%20on%20a%20seamless%20transfer%20of%20power.%20Since%201952%20and%2017%20general%20elections%2C%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%2C%20have%20been%20also%20been%20seen%20as%20among%20the%20freest%20and%20fairest%20in%20the%20region.%20There%20have%20never%20been%20doubts%20about%20the%20election%20monitoring%20body.%20Recent%20events%2C%20including%20the%20sudden%20and%20unexplained%20departure%20of%20Goel%2C%20so%20close%20to%20an%20impending%20election%2C%20cast%20an%20ominous%20shadow%20on%20its%20credibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710212900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F12083734%2F3081307604_2cebd8c3cd_b.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgover